   impl->override_redirect = xattributes.override_redirect;

   /* Sanity checks */
```

@DeeDeeG, I agree that the situation with regarding the executable bit as an indication of trust is not perfect, but it is consistent with Ubuntu's security policy. The policy only applies to files lacking the executable bit, so as far as the policy is concerned, any file that has the executable bit set is allowed to run.

Maybe there is a better way to determine trust (e.g. maintaining a whitelist of trusted file signatures, or making archive tools show a warning when extracting a file that has the executable bit set), but as you say, that topic merits its own discussion and is best left to a separate issue.

__Edit:__ there's now an [__issue to discuss trust and the executable bit__](https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/nautilus/issues/506). Thanks @DeeDeeG!

